Note: this is still just a draft&hellip;
In some of your Scratch projects so far, you might have seen some scripts that look like this:
forever if &lt;key [up arrow v] pressed&gt; then change y by (10) end if &lt;key [down arrow v] pressed&gt; then change y by (-10) end if &lt;key [left arrow v] pressed&gt; then change x by (-10) end if &lt;key [right arrow v] pressed&gt; then change x by (10) end end  This code follows a single line of steps one after the other.
